(RETAIL AI REORDER PREDICTION SYSTEM) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Project Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project is an end-to-end machine learning engineering system for retail reorder prediction) Tj
T*
(using an Instacart-style dataset. It predicts whether a customer is likely to reorder a product) Tj
T*
(based on order history, product behavior, and cart-level signals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project is designed to demonstrate more than model training. It shows how a production-style) Tj
T*
(ML system is structured: data ingestion, feature engineering, training, experiment tracking,) Tj
T*
(model serving, monitoring, CI/CD, and a GenAI assistant layer.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Business Problem) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Retail and grocery platforms need to understand which products a customer is likely to buy) Tj
T*
(again. This helps with:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- personalized recommendations) Tj
T*
(- buy-again sections) Tj
T*
(- targeted promotions) Tj
T*
(- inventory planning) Tj
T*
(- customer retention) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The core prediction question is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Will this customer reorder this product?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The model output is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- 1: likely reordered) Tj
T*
(- 0: not likely reordered) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. End-to-End Workflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The system follows this workflow:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  Raw Instacart data) Tj
T*
(          ->) Tj
T*
(  Ingestion pipeline) Tj
T*
(          ->) Tj
T*
(  Processed data tables) Tj
T*
(          ->) Tj
T*
(  Feature engineering) Tj
T*
(          ->) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
