(- converting raw data to Parquet) Tj
T*
(- joining orders, products, and order-product data) Tj
T*
(- aggregating product and user features) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PySpark requires Java because the Spark execution engine runs on the JVM. Python controls Spark,) Tj
T*
(but Spark itself executes through the JVM.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Pandas) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Pandas is used as a lightweight demo engine for small local data. This allows the project to run) Tj
T*
(without Java or Spark setup during demos.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The demo mode is activated with:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  $env:RETAIL_ENGINE="pandas") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is useful for fast local demonstrations and CI-friendly testing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Parquet) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Parquet is used to store processed and feature data. It is columnar, compressed, and commonly) Tj
T*
(used in data lakes and ML pipelines.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In production, this could be upgraded to Delta Lake for ACID transactions, schema enforcement,) Tj
T*
(and time travel.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Scikit-Learn) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Scikit-learn is used for the baseline ML model. The current model is a Random Forest classifier.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Random Forest is used because it works well as a strong baseline for tabular data and can) Tj
T*
(capture non-linear relationships between customer behavior and reorder probability.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(MLflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(MLflow is used for model lifecycle management.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In this project, MLflow handles:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- experiment tracking) Tj
T*
(- parameter logging) Tj
T*
(- metric logging) Tj
T*
(- model artifact logging where supported) Tj
T*
(- model lifecycle structure) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project currently trains one model type: Random Forest.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(FastAPI) Tj
T*
ET
